WEBVTT

00:52.052 --> 00:54.721
Welcome to Air Canada
nonstop service,

00:54.805 --> 00:56.139
Toronto to Paris.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.473
Our flying time today

00:57.558 --> 01:00.476
is an estimated
7 hours, 20 minutes.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.645
Please check that your
seat belt is fastened

01:02.730 --> 01:05.648
and that your chair back
is in the upright position.

01:05.733 --> 01:08.568
We'll be taking off shortly.

01:09.403 --> 01:10.611
Kate?

01:13.615 --> 01:14.741
Yes?

01:14.825 --> 01:18.035
Are you prepared to have
a pleasant flight?

01:18.120 --> 01:19.412
Yes.

01:19.496 --> 01:22.623
Tell me, Kate, what
are you thinking about?

01:24.793 --> 01:26.919
Twisted steel.

01:27.004 --> 01:27.962
Ball of fire.

01:28.046 --> 01:30.423
A naked baby screaming
for his mother.

01:30.507 --> 01:34.010
Kate, what happened
to your little stone cottage?

01:34.094 --> 01:36.053
Picture it now.

01:36.138 --> 01:39.098
OK.

01:40.350 --> 01:42.602
Oh, my god!

01:42.686 --> 01:44.979
And don't forget
your takeoff mantra.

01:45.063 --> 01:47.607
What are the words you chant
softly in your head?

01:47.691 --> 01:50.943
We're going down!
We're going down!

01:51.028 --> 01:52.028
Kate...

01:53.906 --> 01:54.406
OK.

02:01.622 --> 02:02.789
OK.

02:05.167 --> 02:09.419
I Love Paris In the springtime

02:09.505 --> 02:11.047
I Love...

02:11.882 --> 02:13.299
Hello? Hello?

02:13.383 --> 02:16.302
I really think you gave me
the wrong mantra.

02:17.513 --> 02:20.306
I don't love Paris,
I don't like the French,

02:20.390 --> 02:22.892
and I don't want
to go on this trip.

02:24.228 --> 02:26.979
Oh... god, no!

02:27.064 --> 02:29.190
Kate, you can do this.

02:29.274 --> 02:30.274
I can't do this!

02:30.359 --> 02:34.153
I don't belong
on this airplane!

02:34.238 --> 02:37.156
Let me out of here!

02:37.241 --> 02:39.492
I don't want to die!

02:52.631 --> 02:55.466
Kate, your full refund.

02:58.095 --> 03:00.137
Thank you.

03:00.222 --> 03:01.681
You can get the money back

03:01.765 --> 03:02.765
on my ticket.

03:02.850 --> 03:03.971
Money's not the issue, Kate.

03:03.976 --> 03:08.187
I wanted you to come
with me to exper... What?

03:08.272 --> 03:09.438
Is that them?

03:09.773 --> 03:11.649
I don't want to see
my family tonight.

03:11.733 --> 03:12.859
You never do.

03:12.943 --> 03:15.069
Have you noticed how,
since we're engaged,

03:15.153 --> 03:16.195
they don't knock anymore?

03:16.280 --> 03:17.530
They love you.

03:17.614 --> 03:18.823
My family gives me

03:18.907 --> 03:20.825
an unsigned birthday card.

03:20.909 --> 03:22.243
Kate, come with me.

03:22.327 --> 03:24.203
I'll give you
10 milligrams of valium,

03:24.288 --> 03:25.288
a shot of Stoli,

03:25.372 --> 03:28.499
and we'll be there
before you know it.

03:29.209 --> 03:31.419
How can you not want
to go to Paris?

03:31.503 --> 03:32.545
You're a history teacher.

03:32.629 --> 03:33.588
Shame on you.

03:33.672 --> 03:35.548
Charlie, the French,

03:35.632 --> 03:37.216
you know they hate us.

03:37.301 --> 03:38.384
They smoke.

03:38.468 --> 03:39.719
They have a whole relationship

03:39.803 --> 03:41.721
to dairy products, which
I don't understand.

03:41.805 --> 03:42.930
Kate, something's wrong

03:43.015 --> 03:45.016
with the cable!

03:45.100 --> 03:47.059
Is the box set on three?

03:47.144 --> 03:49.520
A week in Paris with
the man you love?

03:49.605 --> 03:51.063
Suture demonstrations.

03:51.148 --> 03:52.231
Midnight strolls?

03:52.316 --> 03:53.608
Medicare meetings.

03:53.692 --> 03:54.734
The Eiffel Tower.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.736
The Eiffel Tower...

03:56.820 --> 03:58.571
I'd love to see
the Eiffel Tower.

03:58.655 --> 03:59.697
OK, Then.

04:01.742 --> 04:02.992
Great.

04:03.452 --> 04:05.912
I'm not supposed
to leave the country

04:05.996 --> 04:07.705
until my immigration interview.

04:07.789 --> 04:08.915
I'm taking that.

04:09.875 --> 04:11.918
No, no. No, you're not.

04:12.002 --> 04:13.753
Make something up.

04:13.837 --> 04:15.129
Tell them your cousin Bridget

04:15.213 --> 04:16.339
fell in the Seine.

04:16.423 --> 04:17.464
They'll find out

04:17.548 --> 04:18.591
I have no cousin Bridget

04:18.675 --> 04:19.675
and deport me.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.844
Like the one time
I smoked pot...

04:21.928 --> 04:23.471
I didn't want to,

04:23.555 --> 04:25.139
I had a horrible time,

04:25.223 --> 04:27.308
and Ronny Templeton's
little brother

04:27.392 --> 04:29.060
called the police,
and we got arrested.

04:29.144 --> 04:31.687
The one time I ever
did anything illegal.

04:32.356 --> 04:33.481
Bure drops it in...

04:33.565 --> 04:35.775
They put cheese on both pizzas.

04:35.859 --> 04:37.818
Herb, this is you,
you didn't check.

04:37.903 --> 04:38.945
Take it back.

04:39.029 --> 04:40.696
You know Kate hates cheese.

04:40.781 --> 04:41.864
I'll pick it off.

04:41.949 --> 04:44.408
Here's a list of stuff I want.

04:44.493 --> 04:45.743
Forget it. Kate's not going.

04:45.827 --> 04:47.328
I'm not going. Why not?

04:47.412 --> 04:49.497
Is it the French thing?

04:49.581 --> 04:51.248
No, it's the flying thing.

04:51.333 --> 04:54.168
It's not the French thing
or the flying thing.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.795
I'm not supposed to travel

04:55.879 --> 04:57.630
until my Canadian
citizenship clears.

04:57.714 --> 04:59.632
Hon, we got to move it.

04:59.716 --> 05:02.051
Oh, Kate, I almost forgot,

05:02.135 --> 05:03.302
the Merediths

05:03.387 --> 05:05.972
have put their house
on the market.

05:17.109 --> 05:19.360
Why are we looking at
a house we can't afford?

05:19.444 --> 05:22.488
Charlie, there's something
I have to tell you.

05:22.572 --> 05:25.116
Since I turned 21,

05:25.200 --> 05:27.076
I've been putting money
aside every week

05:27.160 --> 05:29.537
into a savings account,

05:29.621 --> 05:31.872
which I then rolled into
high-yield term deposits

05:31.957 --> 05:34.208
with interest rates
close to 14 %.

05:34.292 --> 05:36.085
What are you talking about?

05:36.169 --> 05:37.962
I've made us a nest egg.

05:39.840 --> 05:41.007
How many eggs?

05:41.091 --> 05:41.907
45,782 eggs.

05:47.806 --> 05:50.182
Why didn't you
tell me this before?

05:51.393 --> 05:53.102
I wanted it to be a surprise.

05:53.770 --> 05:54.770
It's a surprise.

05:54.855 --> 05:56.939
It's a big surprise.

05:58.316 --> 06:00.026
So, with a little help
from your parents,

06:00.110 --> 06:02.278
we could probably afford this.

06:04.448 --> 06:06.365
My whole life is passing
before my eyes,

06:06.450 --> 06:08.993
and we don't even
have children yet.

06:13.832 --> 06:14.874
Hey.

06:17.461 --> 06:18.461
Hey.

06:36.480 --> 06:38.689
Come to Paris with me.

06:56.124 --> 06:57.208
Hi. Right on time.

06:57.292 --> 06:58.542
Saved me from the news.

06:58.627 --> 07:00.211
Bonsoir, chérie.

07:00.295 --> 07:02.838
Hey. Hi, how's it going?

07:02.923 --> 07:05.174
Good. It's just one
conference after another,

07:05.258 --> 07:07.259
but this city,
it's amazing, Kate.

07:07.344 --> 07:10.930
It's so beautiful,
it just casts a spell.

07:11.014 --> 07:12.056
How was dinner?

07:12.140 --> 07:13.724
They used this sauce,

07:13.809 --> 07:15.309
it had a taste
I never experienced.

07:15.393 --> 07:17.812
C'était incroyable!

07:17.896 --> 07:21.190
The sauces have
to be incroyables

07:21.274 --> 07:22.441
to cover up the horse meat.

07:22.526 --> 07:24.026
I saw this segment on
60 Minutes...

07:24.111 --> 07:25.861
You keep watching
all those shows,

07:25.946 --> 07:27.613
you'll never leave the house.

07:36.998 --> 07:38.082
Hey!

07:38.166 --> 07:39.208
Hey. I can't talk.

07:39.292 --> 07:41.502
I'm with the guys
at this hip club.

07:41.586 --> 07:42.795
I can't hear you.

07:42.879 --> 07:45.673
Sweetie pie, we need to
talk about the house.

07:45.757 --> 07:46.966
I promise you, tomorrow.

07:47.050 --> 07:49.468
I got to go, hon.
Love you. Bye.

07:55.767 --> 07:57.143
I talked to the broker

07:57.227 --> 08:00.312
and told her we are ready
to make an offer

08:00.397 --> 08:02.523
as soon as I talk to Charlie.

08:02.607 --> 08:03.983
You guys are crazy.

08:04.067 --> 08:05.651
I'm never buying a house

08:05.735 --> 08:07.903
or anything else
worth anything.

08:08.572 --> 08:09.572
Why not?

08:09.656 --> 08:11.490
Because you think you
own something like that,

08:11.575 --> 08:13.868
when, really, it
winds up owning you.

08:13.952 --> 08:14.952
It becomes your life,

08:15.036 --> 08:16.328
and then one night,

08:16.413 --> 08:17.663
someone leaves their cigarette,

08:17.747 --> 08:19.415
and it all burns.

08:22.794 --> 08:23.878
Honey, hello?

08:23.962 --> 08:25.379
Kate? Kate?

08:25.463 --> 08:27.840
Yeah, it's me, Charlie.

08:27.924 --> 08:30.342
Are you all right?
Is something wrong?

08:30.427 --> 08:33.386
No... Yeah...
Something's happened.

08:33.471 --> 08:34.847
What? What's wrong?

08:34.931 --> 08:37.183
Oh, Kate... Kate, I'm just...

08:37.267 --> 08:38.893
I'm just so happy, you know?

08:38.977 --> 08:40.102
I'm just so happy

08:40.187 --> 08:41.437
and so...

08:41.520 --> 08:42.520
Fucked up.

08:42.606 --> 08:44.023
I fucked up, definitely.

08:44.107 --> 08:45.608
But it's destiny, Kate.

08:45.984 --> 08:47.067
That's what it is.

08:47.819 --> 08:49.862
What are you saying?
What's destiny?

08:49.946 --> 08:53.532
Destiny... Oh, Kate.
Well, I met this woman,

08:53.617 --> 08:56.952
this apparition, this goddesse.

08:58.371 --> 08:59.496
Goddesse?

08:59.581 --> 09:01.207
It's French for "goddess,"

09:01.291 --> 09:04.168
and so is she. She's French.

09:04.252 --> 09:06.212
I've never, ever felt
this way before.

09:06.296 --> 09:07.421
I feel I could do anything.

09:07.505 --> 09:08.547
I could rule the world,

09:08.632 --> 09:10.090
climb the highest mountain.

09:10.175 --> 09:12.676
I could walk into
a men's room and pee,

09:12.761 --> 09:15.304
even with some big guy
waiting behind me.

09:15.388 --> 09:18.390
What? What are you saying?

09:18.475 --> 09:20.351
Charlie, are you...

09:20.435 --> 09:23.562
Kate, I'm not coming back.

09:23.647 --> 09:26.649
I'm in love... Kate.

09:27.651 --> 09:29.568
Love, like in a sonnet

09:31.321 --> 09:34.448
Or like a...

09:35.200 --> 09:37.326
Like love.

09:41.164 --> 09:42.748
I'm sorry, Kate.

09:44.668 --> 09:46.502
I'm so sorry.

09:56.513 --> 09:57.513
Charlie?

