I Hate Paris

11:01.911 --> 11:05.164
Oh, Why, Oh, Why
Do I hate Paris?

11:05.248 --> 11:08.417
Because My Love Is there

11:08.501 --> 11:12.671
With His Slut girlfriend

11:18.470 --> 11:19.720
This is my first time flying.

11:19.804 --> 11:22.598
I'm just kind of nervous.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.016
First time.

11:26.978 --> 11:28.604
Do you speak any English?

11:28.688 --> 11:29.897
Didn't your mother

11:29.981 --> 11:31.732
ever teach you about staring?

11:31.816 --> 11:33.984
What do you think,
the plane will crash

11:34.069 --> 11:37.488
and we are on the ground
in a thousand pieces dead?

11:37.572 --> 11:38.732
I promise you, if it happens,

11:38.782 --> 11:40.866
you won't feel a thing.

11:41.826 --> 11:44.453
You're French, aren't you?

11:44.537 --> 11:45.829
Luc Teyssier.

11:46.664 --> 11:48.582
How have you got around
your whole life?

11:48.666 --> 11:50.000
Or do you just stay
in your house

11:50.085 --> 11:51.335
with the doors locked?

11:51.419 --> 11:53.796
I get around
as nature intended,

12:01.471 --> 12:02.471
What was that?

12:02.555 --> 12:03.555
What did she say?

12:03.640 --> 12:04.890
That sounded serious.

12:04.974 --> 12:06.975
The pilot says there is
a crack in the engine,

12:07.060 --> 12:09.311
but he take off anyway.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.646
Ladies and gentlemen,

12:10.730 --> 12:13.232
please remember that
the use of cellular phones

12:13.316 --> 12:14.733
and other electronic devices

12:14.818 --> 12:17.194
is forbidden during takeoff.

12:19.322 --> 12:20.447
I don't know

12:20.532 --> 12:21.907
what they taught you in France,

12:21.991 --> 12:23.075
but rude and interesting

12:23.159 --> 12:24.660
are not the same thing.

12:25.578 --> 12:28.330
Oh! God!

12:51.187 --> 12:53.188
We hope you enjoy the flight.

12:53.273 --> 12:55.441
OK, OK, OK...

12:55.525 --> 12:57.818
OK, OK...

12:57.902 --> 12:59.862
Folks, we're third in line

12:59.946 --> 13:00.946
for takeoff,

13:01.030 --> 13:02.114
so just relax.

13:02.198 --> 13:06.201
We should be in the air
in just a couple of minutes.

13:06.286 --> 13:07.995
I've almost got the
stone cottage going.

13:08.079 --> 13:10.289
Could you please
stop looking at me?

13:10.373 --> 13:11.498
Is incredible.

13:11.583 --> 13:13.125
What? What?

13:13.209 --> 13:15.711
Your every muscle
in your body is tense,

13:15.795 --> 13:17.713
even the lids of your eyes.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.756
Your nostrils are...
Are closing up.

13:19.841 --> 13:21.550
How do you do that?

13:21.634 --> 13:24.720
Me, I love to fly,
especially this moment,

13:24.804 --> 13:27.890
the plane getting ready
to charge the runway,

13:27.974 --> 13:30.893
the engines screaming,
the pressure building,

13:30.977 --> 13:34.396
the force of it slams you
back in the seat,

13:34.481 --> 13:38.400
and then, whoosh,
you are in the air.

13:38.485 --> 13:40.903
Everything else is behind you.

13:40.987 --> 13:43.238
There's only one
other place in life

13:43.323 --> 13:45.991
where I feel this kind
of exhilaration.

13:46.075 --> 13:47.242
Oh, yeah? Where's that?

13:47.327 --> 13:49.453
Oh, no, no, no. Don't tell me.

13:49.537 --> 13:51.163
Just let me guess.

13:51.247 --> 13:54.291
Flight attendants,
prepare for takeoff.

13:54.375 --> 13:55.417
Oh, god.

13:55.502 --> 13:58.754
I don't think I can do this.

14:04.594 --> 14:05.761
Did you ever think

14:05.845 --> 14:07.304
that maybe it is
not the airplane?

14:07.388 --> 14:08.680
What's not the airplane?

14:08.765 --> 14:10.724
That maybe it is something else

14:10.808 --> 14:11.892
you are afraid of.

14:11.976 --> 14:13.018
What?

14:13.102 --> 14:14.061
Must I say it?

14:14.145 --> 14:15.145
Can I stop you?

14:15.230 --> 14:18.273
It is obvious to me.
I know your type.

14:18.358 --> 14:19.399
What type is that?

14:19.484 --> 14:21.610
You're afraid to really live.

14:21.694 --> 14:22.694
Oh, god.

14:22.779 --> 14:24.404
You are afraid of life.

14:24.489 --> 14:26.031
You are afraid of love.

14:26.115 --> 14:27.741
You are afraid of sex.

14:27.825 --> 14:29.034
That is ridiculous.

14:29.118 --> 14:32.371
I can tell from your face
and how you dress

14:32.455 --> 14:34.206
with your little white buttons

14:34.290 --> 14:36.708
all the way up to here.

14:36.793 --> 14:39.419
In bed, you are waiting
under the covers,

14:39.504 --> 14:41.088
the light is going off,

14:41.172 --> 14:42.381
and then, like a rabbit...

14:42.465 --> 14:43.924
What?

14:44.008 --> 14:45.926
What is the matter with you?

14:46.010 --> 14:47.219
You don't know me.

14:47.303 --> 14:48.887
I know that you are afraid...

14:48.972 --> 14:50.138
You don't know what I do,

14:50.223 --> 14:51.932
and Charlie never complained.

14:52.016 --> 14:53.392
Stop that.

14:53.476 --> 14:54.476
There were a few months

14:54.561 --> 14:55.936
where I didn't feel like it.

14:56.020 --> 14:57.938
That was a long time ago,

14:58.022 --> 15:00.732
and I was in between
teaching jobs. Yes.

15:00.817 --> 15:01.817
For you to sit there

15:01.901 --> 15:03.569
with that smug expression

15:03.653 --> 15:05.404
and tell me that
I have a problem

15:05.488 --> 15:07.739
with my life and my Charlie

15:21.170 --> 15:23.755
You're just some
nicotine-saturated

15:23.840 --> 15:26.258
and, sorry to say,
hygiene-deficient

15:26.342 --> 15:27.426
Frenchman!

15:27.510 --> 15:29.553
Look...

15:29.637 --> 15:31.847
What a fantastic view?

15:37.895 --> 15:39.229
Now, if you will excuse me,

15:39.314 --> 15:42.774
I must go do
as nature intended.

15:42.859 --> 15:44.151
Pardon, monsieur.

16:03.838 --> 16:07.674
Sir, I'm sorry,
there's no smoking on this plane.

16:07.759 --> 16:10.552
OK, then can I have
two glasses with ice?

16:32.617 --> 16:35.243
Excuse me. Can I
ask you something?

16:36.663 --> 16:38.914
It's Luke, isn't it?

16:38.998 --> 16:41.333
Luc.

16:41.417 --> 16:43.543
No, not Luc... Luc.

16:43.628 --> 16:45.003
Luc?

16:47.048 --> 16:48.590
You want to ask me
something, or no?

16:48.675 --> 16:49.925
No. Forget it.

16:50.009 --> 16:52.010
I forget already.

16:52.095 --> 16:56.306
Did you mean all
that stuff you said,

16:56.391 --> 16:57.849
or were you just
trying to anger me?

16:57.934 --> 16:59.351
Do I look like
the kind of person

16:59.435 --> 17:01.075
that doesn't know
how to have a good time?

17:01.104 --> 17:05.648
You were how old
when you lost it?

17:05.733 --> 17:07.608
It? What it?

17:07.694 --> 17:10.362
You know, it. Your flower.

17:10.445 --> 17:11.863
My flower.

17:11.948 --> 17:14.366
My flower is none
of your business.

17:14.450 --> 17:16.535
I ask you because some people,

17:16.618 --> 17:18.537
they rush toward
the fateful moment,

17:18.621 --> 17:21.330
their bodies bursting
to discover.

17:21.415 --> 17:23.750
Others, they guard it
like some precious gift,

17:23.835 --> 17:24.960
and they wait and wait.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.712
You, I suppose, rushed.

17:26.796 --> 17:28.046
Like a bull.

17:28.131 --> 17:30.424
I have a clear
picture in my mind.

17:30.508 --> 17:31.550
A young bull.

17:31.634 --> 17:32.718
How young?

17:33.136 --> 17:34.177
13.

17:34.262 --> 17:35.470
13?

17:35.555 --> 17:36.888
No, you are right.

17:36.973 --> 17:39.516
I was 12. Magda.

17:39.600 --> 17:41.268
She was a putain...

17:41.352 --> 17:42.561
A...prostitute.

17:42.645 --> 17:44.896
She lived just outside
of my town,

17:44.981 --> 17:45.981
just by a little bridge.

17:46.065 --> 17:48.608
She was... Not beautiful,

17:48.693 --> 17:50.902
but she had this mouth.

17:50.987 --> 17:53.405
Oh, there was another
world waiting there.

17:53.489 --> 17:55.407
But I did not have
the money for the kissing.

17:55.491 --> 17:57.534
Only for the... You know.

17:57.618 --> 17:58.785
I don't understand.

17:58.870 --> 18:00.829
To kiss a prostitute,
it costs more.

18:00.913 --> 18:02.080
It has always been.

18:02.165 --> 18:04.499
Oh, well, that makes sense.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.501
A kiss is so... So intimate.

18:06.586 --> 18:07.919
You could probably disconnect

18:08.004 --> 18:10.505
from everything else,
but a kiss...

18:10.590 --> 18:12.215
Two people's lips together,

18:12.300 --> 18:13.341
and their breath,

18:13.426 --> 18:15.969
a little bit of their souls...

18:21.893 --> 18:23.560
All I mean is that a kiss

18:23.644 --> 18:24.978
is where the romance is.

18:25.062 --> 18:26.855
That is what I thought back then,

18:26.939 --> 18:29.941
so I stole 50 francs
from my brother Antoine,

18:30.026 --> 18:31.067
and I went back,

18:31.152 --> 18:32.444
and I kissed Magda
for half an hour.

18:32.528 --> 18:33.779
It was very good.

18:35.698 --> 18:37.032
Now you.

18:37.950 --> 18:38.950
Now me what?

18:39.035 --> 18:40.035
It is your turn.

18:40.119 --> 18:41.411
I tell you, now you tell me.

18:41.496 --> 18:43.371
I am all ears.

18:44.207 --> 18:46.374
All right. Yeah...

18:46.459 --> 18:48.710
No, I didn't... I...

18:48.795 --> 18:50.170
I didn't rush, you were right,

18:50.254 --> 18:52.130
but I didn't hide
from it, either.

18:52.215 --> 18:53.507
I wanted it to be great.

18:53.591 --> 18:56.218
I was... 18.

18:57.220 --> 18:58.804
Jeff the jock.

18:58.888 --> 19:01.681
My basement. Valentine's day.

19:01.766 --> 19:04.059
Jeopardy! In the background.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.477
It's a game show on TV.

19:05.561 --> 19:07.813
Jeopardy! We have it.

19:07.897 --> 19:09.097
Jeff said it would last longer

19:09.106 --> 19:12.484
with the show on
to distract him.

19:12.568 --> 19:13.689
He got all the answers wrong

19:13.736 --> 19:15.153
except for sports.

19:15.822 --> 19:17.823
By double Jeopardy!,
he was done.

19:17.907 --> 19:18.907
By final Jeopardy!,

19:18.991 --> 19:21.868
he was on his way home, so...

19:21.953 --> 19:23.829
Yeah, the first time was bad,

19:23.913 --> 19:25.622
but since then, it's
been mainly good,

19:25.706 --> 19:27.027
and then I found
somebody special,

19:27.083 --> 19:28.416
so it was great.

19:31.879 --> 19:33.088
Could I ask you something?

19:35.383 --> 19:36.591
Do you believe in love,

19:36.676 --> 19:38.426
the kind that lasts forever?

19:41.138 --> 19:42.722
I loved my mother.

19:42.807 --> 19:45.058
No. Everybody
loves their mother,

19:45.142 --> 19:47.185
even people who
hate their mothers.

19:47.270 --> 19:49.187
Is one man meant for one woman?

19:49.272 --> 19:50.397
That is the question.

19:50.481 --> 19:52.607
It is not
an interesting question.

19:52.692 --> 19:54.860
It is the question
of a little girl

19:54.944 --> 19:56.862
who believes in fairy tales.

19:56.946 --> 19:58.530
It's an everyone question,

19:58.614 --> 19:59.781
one that everybody thinks

19:59.866 --> 20:00.907
they have the answer to,

20:00.992 --> 20:03.910
until, one day,
something happens.

20:04.620 --> 20:05.954
Something happened?

20:10.293 --> 20:12.627
Look, I understand.
I understand.

20:12.712 --> 20:13.879
One love for you

20:13.963 --> 20:15.338
would be like
having to eat home

20:15.423 --> 20:17.465
for the rest of your life...

20:17.550 --> 20:19.384
And you probably like to go out

20:19.468 --> 20:21.052
to a different restaurant

20:21.137 --> 20:22.262
every chance you get.

20:23.431 --> 20:24.389
Careful, now.

20:24.473 --> 20:25.473
What's that?

20:25.558 --> 20:26.558
It is nothing.

20:26.642 --> 20:28.101
Are you hiding something?

20:28.185 --> 20:29.436
I have to go.

20:30.688 --> 20:32.105
I have to go again.

20:32.189 --> 20:33.231
Again?

20:52.543 --> 20:53.960
Parfait.

21:48.516 --> 21:50.934
Why'd you let me drink so much?

21:51.018 --> 21:52.339
Me? I did not let you
do anything.

21:52.395 --> 21:53.812
You did it yourself.

21:54.855 --> 21:57.857
And I will give you
a ride into Paris, OK.?

21:57.942 --> 22:01.361
It will save you a lot
of money, believe me.

22:01.445 --> 22:04.572
After what we have been
through together...

22:04.657 --> 22:06.408
Where are you staying?

22:06.492 --> 22:08.076
George V.

22:12.790 --> 22:15.208
"Nothing to declare."
That is you.

22:15.292 --> 22:16.334
Me, they're going to stop.

22:16.419 --> 22:17.460
They always do.

22:17.545 --> 22:20.505
I meet you outside,
one minute maximum.

22:26.721 --> 22:28.513
Your passport and plane ticket.

22:34.770 --> 22:36.813
Would you open your bag?

22:37.940 --> 22:39.274
Wait for me.

22:40.526 --> 22:42.819
That won't be necessary.

22:43.529 --> 22:44.863
What are you doing here?

22:45.281 --> 22:47.615
Don't you think
a cop gets a vacation?

22:50.411 --> 22:52.078
Give him back his papers.

22:59.795 --> 23:03.298
Look... there's Louise.

23:06.802 --> 23:11.056
I need a taxi to the
George V in Paris.

23:13.309 --> 23:15.477
I'll call you Monday.
We'll have a drink.

23:15.644 --> 23:19.647
Why wait till Monday?

23:20.316 --> 23:22.650
I've got something...

23:24.737 --> 23:26.488
Never mind... let's go.

23:36.457 --> 23:38.625
Papa, why are you looking
through the man's things?

23:40.878 --> 23:43.838
The same reason I look
through your room when you're asleep.

23:44.048 --> 23:47.008
To protect my loved ones
from themselves.

23:47.134 --> 23:48.510
You won't find anything in there.

23:49.136 --> 23:51.012
Are you really a thief?

23:51.097 --> 23:53.515
Me?

23:55.226 --> 23:56.851
Daddy says you saved his life.

23:56.936 --> 24:00.230
It's true. You see this little scar?

24:00.314 --> 24:03.233
Luc stopped it
from going all the way over here.

24:03.317 --> 24:06.486
He's no criminal.
That's what I keep telling him.

24:06.862 --> 24:09.072
To the left, Louise.

24:25.172 --> 24:26.506
Oui, madame?

24:26.590 --> 24:28.716
Yes, bonjour.

24:28.801 --> 24:30.885
Do you speak any English?

24:30.970 --> 24:33.221
Of course.
This is the George V,

24:33.305 --> 24:34.973
not some backpacker's hovel.

24:35.057 --> 24:37.100
Hovel?

24:37.184 --> 24:38.560
Of course not.

24:38.644 --> 24:39.811
Could you tell me which room

24:39.895 --> 24:41.771
Charlie Lytton is
staying in, please?

24:42.898 --> 24:45.775
Dr. Charles Lytton.
He's expecting me.

24:45.860 --> 24:47.986
I'm afraid no.

24:48.070 --> 24:49.112
No?

24:49.196 --> 24:50.238
No, madame.

24:50.322 --> 24:53.158
Perhaps madame could try
the courtesy phone.

24:54.285 --> 24:56.536
Well, madame has tried
the courtesy phone.

24:56.620 --> 24:58.079
Do not disturb.

25:00.958 --> 25:03.501
Look, I just spent

25:03.586 --> 25:06.379
seven hours on an airplane

25:08.924 --> 25:10.842
I'm tired, and I'm hungry,

25:10.926 --> 25:12.760
and I just want
to see my fiancé.

25:12.845 --> 25:14.888
Now, are you going to help me?

25:14.972 --> 25:18.183
It is my duty
to vigorously safeguard

25:18.267 --> 25:20.185
the privacy of our guests,

25:20.269 --> 25:22.228
and if our guests
need safeguarding

25:22.313 --> 25:23.730
from their own fiancées,

25:23.814 --> 25:26.649
well, after all,
unlike some countries,

25:26.734 --> 25:29.861
France is not a nation
of puritanical hypocrites.

25:41.790 --> 25:42.916
Hey.

25:43.000 --> 25:44.918
Hey, hey, hey.

25:46.045 --> 25:48.254
I just gave you 100 francs.

25:48.339 --> 25:49.464
Oui, madame,

25:49.548 --> 25:51.216
and I took it. Merci.

25:51.300 --> 25:54.093
If there is
anything else I can do,

25:54.178 --> 25:55.678
please let me know.

26:29.838 --> 26:31.506
Bonjour, mademoiselle.

26:31.590 --> 26:33.174
You are American, no?

26:36.762 --> 26:38.346
For the moment.

26:38.430 --> 26:39.889
Well, forgive me for intruding,

26:39.974 --> 26:41.933
but I saw you sitting here,

26:42.017 --> 26:43.393
looking a little sad.

26:43.477 --> 26:45.728
Why should such
a beautiful woman

26:45.813 --> 26:47.772
look so sad, I asked myself.

26:47.856 --> 26:49.941
Have you got an hour?

26:50.025 --> 26:51.442
As a matter of fact,

26:51.527 --> 26:53.111
always.

26:54.822 --> 26:57.699
Let me help you
to forget your sadness.

26:57.783 --> 26:59.367
Remember you are in Paris,

26:59.451 --> 27:01.369
City of Love.

27:02.162 --> 27:03.204
Can I ask you something?

27:03.289 --> 27:04.372
Of course.

27:04.456 --> 27:05.832
Can you urinate

27:05.916 --> 27:07.834
with someone standing
right behind you?

27:09.920 --> 27:12.463
I think I could manage it.

27:15.592 --> 27:18.011
Are you going
to be the someone?

27:20.597 --> 27:24.017
Me? No. That's not
what I meant.

27:24.810 --> 27:26.352
So...

27:26.437 --> 27:28.354
You would like that I arrange

27:28.439 --> 27:31.232
for someone else
to stand next to me?

27:31.317 --> 27:32.859
It could be arranged.

27:32.943 --> 27:35.737
Perhaps Pierre, Monique...

27:36.572 --> 27:38.364
You have the face of an angel,

27:38.449 --> 27:42.243
but I'm delighted to find
the mind is a little devil.

27:42.328 --> 27:43.369
Hey, hey,

27:43.454 --> 27:44.871
look, Mister,

27:44.955 --> 27:46.372
this will get you nowhere.

27:46.457 --> 27:48.541
I'm waiting to meet my fiancé.

27:48.625 --> 27:50.376
If he sees you bothering me,

27:50.461 --> 27:52.170
even talking to me,

27:52.254 --> 27:54.005
he'll walk right over here...

28:43.180 --> 28:45.556
What are you doing here?
You only work the metro.

28:45.641 --> 28:49.477
No more.
With this suit, I'm a new man.

28:57.486 --> 28:58.694
Charlie?

29:00.906 --> 29:03.991
Hey, you said you'd
give me a ride.

29:04.076 --> 29:06.035
You said... Where are we?

29:06.120 --> 29:07.120
Your hotel.

29:07.204 --> 29:09.038
I take you to your room.

29:09.123 --> 29:10.498
I don't have a room.

29:10.582 --> 29:11.999
Someone has taken my room,

29:12.084 --> 29:15.044
someone in 4-inch heels,
a red dress...

29:16.505 --> 29:17.880
Oh, my god.

29:17.965 --> 29:19.465
My bags.

29:19.550 --> 29:20.591
What?

29:20.676 --> 29:22.009
My bags are gone.

29:22.094 --> 29:23.886
What? They can't be gone.

29:23.971 --> 29:25.221
How can they?

29:25.305 --> 29:26.472
Why look under there?

29:26.557 --> 29:29.851
I didn't lose my keys.
I lost my suitcase!

29:29.935 --> 29:32.895
Where did you put them down?

29:32.980 --> 29:34.355
I fainted right there.

29:34.440 --> 29:37.442
Oh, my money, my passport,
my vitamins...

29:37.526 --> 29:38.651
May I be of service?

29:43.824 --> 29:45.283
You tell him!

29:45.367 --> 29:47.034
How could you let this happen?

29:47.119 --> 29:48.411
What is your problem?

29:48.495 --> 29:50.204
They're my bags!

29:50.289 --> 29:53.082
I am upset because
it is my country

29:53.167 --> 29:54.250
and this is a scandal.

29:54.334 --> 29:55.960
Do you remember anything?

29:56.044 --> 29:57.295
I was sitting here,

29:57.379 --> 30:00.465
then that guy came
and talked to me...

30:00.549 --> 30:02.758
Then I saw Charlie.

30:02.843 --> 30:04.427
Oh, here we go again.

30:04.511 --> 30:05.553
Here. Sit, sit, sit.

30:05.637 --> 30:07.555
Breathe in... Breathe out...

30:07.639 --> 30:08.639
Breathe in...

30:08.724 --> 30:09.849
I'm breathing!

30:09.933 --> 30:11.225
You know, all men are bastards.

30:11.310 --> 30:13.644
Well, some are just
trying to help.

30:13.729 --> 30:16.272
I never thought I'd say this,

30:16.356 --> 30:17.565
but it's true.

30:17.649 --> 30:18.900
All men are bastards.

30:18.984 --> 30:20.735
The guy talking to you,

30:20.819 --> 30:22.236
- he was...
- A bastard.

30:22.321 --> 30:24.572
A Euro-trash-in-Armani bastard.

30:24.656 --> 30:26.866
He wore a black suit
with a yellow shirt?

30:26.950 --> 30:28.242
Yeah.

30:28.327 --> 30:29.619
- You know him?
- Come.

30:29.703 --> 30:30.745
Of course.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.914
All you bastards
know each other.

30:34.374 --> 30:35.500
Bastard.

30:38.420 --> 30:39.670
All right, all right.

30:39.755 --> 30:41.172
You wait here,

30:41.256 --> 30:43.758
I go get the... My car,

30:43.842 --> 30:46.886
and we go get your stuff, OK.?

31:27.302 --> 31:29.845
So who's this guy
who stole my bags?

31:29.930 --> 31:32.306
Bub.

31:32.391 --> 31:33.641
Bub?

31:33.725 --> 31:35.142
No, Bub.

31:35.227 --> 31:36.644
Bub, like...

31:36.728 --> 31:37.812
Bub Dylan.

31:37.896 --> 31:39.230
Bob.

31:39.314 --> 31:41.065
Oui. Bahhb.

31:41.149 --> 31:43.234
Now, why are you helping me?

31:43.318 --> 31:44.443
Why?

31:44.528 --> 31:46.821
Because I like you.

31:46.905 --> 31:47.905
I do...

31:47.990 --> 31:49.198
But I don't like

31:49.283 --> 31:50.866
how you say on the plane

31:50.951 --> 31:53.119
with your face
all scrunched up,

31:53.203 --> 31:55.413
"You're French, aren't you?"

31:55.497 --> 31:56.664
I don't like how you say

31:56.748 --> 31:58.207
with your eyes all squinty,

31:58.292 --> 32:00.376
"All men are bastards."

32:00.460 --> 32:01.586
Scrunched?

32:03.755 --> 32:05.131
Allons-y! Allons-y!

32:05.215 --> 32:06.549
Allez, allez!

32:12.973 --> 32:15.266
Please don't break
the car, OK.?

32:23.942 --> 32:26.611
OK, so I try to understand.

32:26.695 --> 32:29.780
He says he has met
this woman...

32:29.865 --> 32:31.616
no, no. This goddess.

32:31.700 --> 32:33.951
He breaks your heart.

32:34.036 --> 32:35.786
He...

32:35.871 --> 32:37.455
Hurts me.

32:37.539 --> 32:38.581
Humbles me.

32:38.665 --> 32:39.707
Humiliates you.

32:39.791 --> 32:40.791
Humiliates me.

32:40.876 --> 32:43.002
So you come here to Paris

32:43.086 --> 32:44.712
so he can do it again,

32:44.796 --> 32:46.881
but this time, in your face.

32:46.965 --> 32:48.132
No.

32:50.427 --> 32:51.469
Pardon.

32:51.553 --> 32:53.471
No, no. I come to Paris

32:53.555 --> 32:55.640
to get back the man
that I love.

32:55.724 --> 32:56.974
Is that so hard to understand,

32:57.059 --> 32:58.768
even for someone like yourself?

32:58.852 --> 33:01.228
OK, and meanwhile,
his lover is...

33:01.313 --> 33:03.731
Don't ever use that word again.

33:03.815 --> 33:05.232
This bastard woman,

33:05.317 --> 33:07.777
she is feeling something else,

33:07.861 --> 33:09.320
maybe...

33:09.404 --> 33:12.239
Once he saw me, myself, moi,

33:12.324 --> 33:14.575
everything would change.
The spell would be broken.

33:15.744 --> 33:18.412
What, you don't think
I could change his mind?

33:18.497 --> 33:20.790
I would remind him
we had a wonderful,

33:20.874 --> 33:21.999
perfect life together.

33:22.084 --> 33:23.125
Evidently.

33:23.210 --> 33:25.336
I've never been so happy.

33:25.420 --> 33:26.712
When someone says that,

33:26.797 --> 33:28.422
my ass begins to twitch.

33:28.507 --> 33:31.801
And we had plans
for a home and family.

33:31.885 --> 33:33.511
I'd remind him of that, too.

33:33.595 --> 33:35.888
He was obviously
very attached to them.

33:35.972 --> 33:37.556
If all else failed...

33:37.641 --> 33:40.226
You'd get down
on your knees and beg?

33:40.310 --> 33:41.519
It's possible.

33:41.603 --> 33:42.770
I can see it,

33:42.854 --> 33:44.980
there is the goddess
standing next to Charlie

33:45.065 --> 33:46.273
in her negligee,

33:46.358 --> 33:48.693
and you are on
your knees, begging.

33:48.777 --> 33:49.985
Poor Charlie.

33:50.070 --> 33:51.779
Tough decision.

33:56.034 --> 33:57.451
Alors!

33:58.995 --> 34:00.746
I didn't beg.

34:00.831 --> 34:02.498
No. You fainted.

34:06.670 --> 34:08.670
Hey, Luc-a-doo!

34:14.969 --> 34:19.098
I see how far you'd go
for the love of your life.

34:19.181 --> 34:20.891
If you know so much,

34:20.976 --> 34:23.393
how come no one greeted
you at the airport?

34:23.478 --> 34:25.730
Please. I'm finished
with women, OK.?

34:25.813 --> 34:27.398
Haven't found the right one?

34:27.482 --> 34:29.400
I have found plenty,
believe me.

34:29.484 --> 34:30.818
Afraid of commitment.

34:30.902 --> 34:32.194
I'm afraid of nothing.

34:32.279 --> 34:34.029
I know your problem,
no staying power.

34:34.114 --> 34:35.239
What?

34:35.322 --> 34:36.364
You can't stick it out.

34:36.449 --> 34:38.051
- What you talking about?
- It's obvious.

34:38.118 --> 34:39.243
It is?

34:39.327 --> 34:42.079
You are afraid of commitment.

34:42.164 --> 34:43.789
Commitment! Oh, OK., sorry.

34:43.873 --> 34:45.123
I thought you meant...

34:45.208 --> 34:46.292
What did you think?

34:46.376 --> 34:48.043
Nothing. It's OK.

34:48.128 --> 34:50.129
This problem.

34:50.213 --> 34:52.089
It's not a problem!

34:52.174 --> 34:53.424
For you, Luc?

34:53.507 --> 34:55.092
Every man goes through that.

34:55.177 --> 34:57.052
Charlie never did,
but, you know,

34:57.137 --> 34:59.013
it's usually an issue
of self-esteem.

34:59.097 --> 35:01.390
It's just a recent
phenomenon, OK.?

35:01.475 --> 35:03.893
I've been under a lot
of pressure recently.

35:03.977 --> 35:06.020
Soon it will all be over,

35:06.104 --> 35:08.731
and then zip, boom, bonjour,

35:08.815 --> 35:11.025
I'm back in business, OK.?

35:21.286 --> 35:22.536
Bob, great to see you.

35:22.871 --> 35:23.829
Hi, Luc.

35:23.914 --> 35:25.581
You've met my friend Kate?

35:25.874 --> 35:27.041
Hello again.

35:31.421 --> 35:32.463
Where's the rest?

35:32.547 --> 35:33.547
Hey!

35:39.095 --> 35:41.806
What about my money
and my passport?

35:43.850 --> 35:46.852
He sold the passport.
First thing to go.

35:46.937 --> 35:50.397
What about my suitcase

35:50.482 --> 35:51.649
and my clothes?

35:51.733 --> 35:53.025
Ask him about my vitamins.

35:54.444 --> 35:55.778
Her clothes?

35:56.530 --> 35:58.447
I gave them to Monique.

35:58.573 --> 35:59.657
Monique?

35:59.741 --> 36:01.826
What? What? What did he say?

36:01.910 --> 36:03.536
He threw them away.

36:05.330 --> 36:07.915
Oh, god!

36:07.999 --> 36:10.417
Oh, man!

36:12.671 --> 36:14.421
God!

36:15.799 --> 36:18.133
What? No. No, thank you.

36:20.387 --> 36:23.055
You got rid of everything?

36:28.562 --> 36:30.563
Except for that...

36:52.210 --> 36:54.378
You hid a plant in my bag?

36:54.462 --> 36:56.380
Not just a plant. A vine.

36:56.464 --> 36:57.585
That's why you're helping me.

36:57.591 --> 36:59.466
You don't give a shit about me.

36:59.593 --> 37:01.176
I'm sorry you lost your stuff,

37:01.261 --> 37:04.096
but it was not me who stole it.

37:04.180 --> 37:07.057
What if I had gotten
stopped at customs?

37:07.142 --> 37:08.559
What would've happened then?

37:08.643 --> 37:10.060
Don't be ridiculous.

37:10.145 --> 37:11.729
People like you
they don't stop.

37:11.813 --> 37:14.231
Why do you think I choose you?

37:14.316 --> 37:16.567
You'd declare a pack
of chewing gum.

37:16.651 --> 37:18.652
Please, don't ever, ever...

37:20.488 --> 37:22.156
Never touch my vine.

37:23.325 --> 37:24.909
You don't understand. This...

37:24.993 --> 37:26.994
This is my future.

37:27.078 --> 37:29.413
I'm going to make
a great vineyard,

37:29.497 --> 37:31.790
and I'm going to escape
this shit hole.

37:33.501 --> 37:34.793
You can't make a vineyard

37:34.878 --> 37:35.878
out of one vine.

37:35.962 --> 37:37.421
No. Not one vine.

37:37.505 --> 37:39.089
I take this little
American vine,

37:39.174 --> 37:41.091
I mix it with others,

37:41.176 --> 37:42.927
then I make something new.

37:43.011 --> 37:44.929
I don't care. I don't care.

37:45.013 --> 37:46.138
Why listen to you?

37:46.222 --> 37:47.431
It's bullshit.

37:47.515 --> 37:48.849
Everything with you
is bullshit.

37:48.934 --> 37:50.017
OK, fine.

37:50.101 --> 37:51.185
Go home.

37:51.269 --> 37:53.437
Find a nice little boy
you can boss around.

37:53.521 --> 37:56.440
Only don't let him
out of your sight.

37:56.524 --> 37:57.942
How do I do that?

37:58.026 --> 38:00.110
I have no money, no ticket,

38:00.195 --> 38:01.779
no passport...

38:01.863 --> 38:03.364
Here. Take this. Please.

38:03.448 --> 38:04.490
I don't want your money.

38:04.574 --> 38:06.784
It's what he got
for your stuff.

38:06.868 --> 38:08.911
I don't want your money.

38:08.995 --> 38:10.621
Now go away.

38:10.705 --> 38:12.706
Stop following me.

38:13.667 --> 38:15.417
OK.

38:15.502 --> 38:17.002
Bonne chance.

39:11.349 --> 39:13.767
What necklace?

39:13.935 --> 39:15.644
I didn't see any necklace!

39:15.854 --> 39:17.646
It must still be in her bag!

39:19.232 --> 39:20.649
In her bag?

39:59.773 --> 40:02.816
It's Wonderful... It's wonderful

40:02.901 --> 40:04.068
It's Wonderful

40:04.152 --> 40:06.028
Good Luck, My Baby

40:07.322 --> 40:09.865
It's Wonderful... It's wonderful

40:09.949 --> 40:13.744
I Dream Of You Chips, chips

40:42.941 --> 40:45.943
It's Wonderful... It's wonderful

40:46.027 --> 40:47.444
It's Wonderful

40:47.529 --> 40:49.238
Good Luck, My Baby

40:49.322 --> 40:51.990
It's Wonderful... It's wonderful

40:52.075 --> 40:53.283
It's Wonderful

40:53.368 --> 40:55.035
I Dream Of You

40:55.120 --> 40:57.287
Chips, Chips

41:01.501 --> 41:04.128
You are currently
a resident of Canada

41:04.212 --> 41:06.922
in the process of applying
for Canadian citizenship?

41:07.006 --> 41:09.258
My fiancé is Canadian.

41:09.342 --> 41:11.552
Let me ask you something.

41:11.636 --> 41:13.470
You no longer want
to be an American,

41:13.555 --> 41:14.596
but you expect me

41:14.681 --> 41:16.348
to give you a new passport?

41:17.684 --> 41:19.518
Is this a trick question?

41:19.602 --> 41:20.811
I'll need a copy

41:20.895 --> 41:22.146
of your Canadian resident visa

41:22.230 --> 41:24.648
before I can process
your application.

41:24.732 --> 41:25.732
Next.

41:38.580 --> 41:39.663
OK.

41:39.747 --> 41:41.123
How it works is,

41:41.207 --> 41:42.833
I ask you a question,

41:42.917 --> 41:44.418
and you comment.

41:46.045 --> 41:48.505
You weren't supposed
to leave Canada?

41:50.258 --> 41:51.633
Yeah, I know that,

41:51.718 --> 41:53.468
but an emergency
situation arose,

41:53.553 --> 41:55.470
and I needed to...

41:55.555 --> 41:57.389
What are you writing down?

41:57.473 --> 41:59.391
Why didn't you
request permission

41:59.475 --> 42:01.894
to leave for your emergency?

42:01.978 --> 42:04.062
Well, I should have, I realize.

42:04.147 --> 42:05.898
But an emergency,
by definition,

42:05.982 --> 42:07.941
doesn't give you the time.

42:08.026 --> 42:11.403
See, the thing is, sir,

42:11.487 --> 42:14.406
I want to be a Canadian
more than anything.

42:14.490 --> 42:17.409
I want to be just like you.

42:17.493 --> 42:18.619
Believe me.

42:18.703 --> 42:21.788
I just want to go home.

42:21.873 --> 42:22.956
What's that?

42:26.377 --> 42:27.669
OK.

42:30.381 --> 42:31.882
Have you...

42:31.966 --> 42:34.134
Ever been convicted...

42:34.219 --> 42:35.928
Of a felony?

42:39.891 --> 42:41.266
No.

42:45.480 --> 42:47.189
Yes.

42:47.273 --> 42:48.273
OK.

42:48.358 --> 42:50.817
OK, I was at
Ronny Templeton's house,

42:50.902 --> 42:52.402
and somebody handed me...

42:52.487 --> 42:53.862
All right,
it wasn't a cigarette,

42:53.947 --> 42:55.280
peer pressure.

42:55.365 --> 42:56.907
Peer pressure's
a terrible thing

42:56.991 --> 42:59.368
when you're a girl in college.

42:59.452 --> 43:01.870
Thing is, we just received this

43:01.955 --> 43:03.247
from a Sergeant Patton

43:03.331 --> 43:04.748
at the American Embassy.

43:04.832 --> 43:06.500
It says you were once convicted

43:06.584 --> 43:09.336
for possession of a narcotic.

43:12.006 --> 43:14.258
Is marijuana really a narcotic?

43:14.342 --> 43:16.760
I mean, it was
just the one time,

43:16.844 --> 43:18.762
and I didn't even enjoy it.

43:18.846 --> 43:21.431
I inhaled,
but then I was coughing

43:21.516 --> 43:23.267
and hacking away
for 10 minutes.

43:23.351 --> 43:24.726
I hate that.

43:25.520 --> 43:26.853
You do?

43:27.522 --> 43:28.939
Well, the point is

43:29.023 --> 43:31.525
is that you didn't
include this information

43:31.609 --> 43:33.944
in your application for
Canadian citizenship,

43:34.028 --> 43:35.779
paragraph 5, article 1?

43:37.448 --> 43:38.448
OK.

43:40.868 --> 43:42.286
Here's where I tell you

43:42.370 --> 43:44.037
that your request
for a new residence visa

43:44.122 --> 43:45.622
has been denied.

44:27.498 --> 44:28.540
Merci.

44:42.221 --> 44:44.306
Yeah. He proposed to her.

44:44.390 --> 44:45.807
He's such an asshole.

44:45.892 --> 44:47.768
I just can't believe it.

44:47.852 --> 44:50.312
Do I have to be friends
with Juliette?

44:50.396 --> 44:51.438
Lilly...

44:51.522 --> 44:53.940
Lilly, now, stop it, all right?

44:54.025 --> 44:55.400
He's not going to marry her.

44:55.485 --> 44:57.486
Now, tell me
everything you know.

44:57.570 --> 44:59.371
They're going somewhere
in the south of France

44:59.405 --> 45:00.489
to meet her parents,

45:00.573 --> 45:03.033
then they're getting married.

45:03.117 --> 45:05.911
We're not even invited.
Not that I'd go...

45:05.995 --> 45:07.954
Lilly, now, listen, OK?

45:08.039 --> 45:10.791
This is very important.
Very important.

45:10.875 --> 45:12.209
You have to tell me

45:12.293 --> 45:15.712
exactly where they're going
and when, all right?

45:15.797 --> 45:18.423
Now, just... just ask mom.

45:18.508 --> 45:20.884
She has it all
written down probably.

45:20.968 --> 45:22.344
OK.

45:22.428 --> 45:24.137
You still supposed
to call her mom?

45:24.222 --> 45:25.263
Lilly!

45:25.348 --> 45:26.640
OK.

45:26.724 --> 45:27.891
Mom!

45:29.811 --> 45:32.396
Kate? Is that you, sweetheart?

45:32.480 --> 45:35.357
I've got all the information
written down,

45:35.441 --> 45:37.150
but I think you can
still get him

45:37.235 --> 45:38.777
at the hotel in Paris.

45:40.655 --> 45:42.864
My god, she's crying.

45:42.949 --> 45:44.950
It's OK. I'm not crying.

45:45.034 --> 45:47.452
I'm just...

45:47.537 --> 45:50.747
I'm just...

45:50.832 --> 45:53.417
I'm going to get him back, mom.

45:53.501 --> 45:54.918
I'm going to get him back,

45:55.002 --> 45:56.670
and I'm going to
make him love me,

45:56.754 --> 45:59.423
and we're going to live
happily ever after.

46:00.466 --> 46:04.094
And I'm just crying now in...

46:04.178 --> 46:05.512
Happiness...

46:06.514 --> 46:09.099
Because I know...

46:09.183 --> 46:12.853
I know I will...

46:12.937 --> 46:14.688
I will triumph.

46:21.362 --> 46:22.946
What do they call the beaches?

46:24.157 --> 46:25.157
What does it mean?

46:25.241 --> 46:26.324
The blue coast.

46:26.409 --> 46:28.785
The blue coast,
lying there next to you.

46:28.870 --> 46:32.289
And we're going
to land in Nice.

46:32.373 --> 46:33.331
Nice?

46:33.416 --> 46:34.416
Yes.

46:34.500 --> 46:35.459
That's nice.

46:35.543 --> 46:36.585
Sweet.

47:02.945 --> 47:05.614
Bob, you know how it works.

47:06.532 --> 47:09.576
If the little fish is to survive,
he must tell the fisherman...

47:09.660 --> 47:11.578
where the big fish are.

47:11.913 --> 47:14.164
Forget it, I'm no rat.

47:16.542 --> 47:20.212
You're mixing your metaphors.

47:20.421 --> 47:22.172
Who buys the passports?

47:28.930 --> 47:31.306
Hi there.

47:31.390 --> 47:33.475
Welcome back, madame,
to the George V.

47:35.436 --> 47:37.020
It's incredible
how you do that.

47:37.104 --> 47:39.022
The words come out
"welcome back,"

47:39.106 --> 47:41.441
but the meaning is
completely different.

47:41.526 --> 47:44.486
Is that a French thing
or a concierge thing?

47:44.570 --> 47:45.904
As madame wishes.

47:45.988 --> 47:48.448
You did it again.

47:49.116 --> 47:50.200
Tell me something,

47:50.284 --> 47:51.868
because I... I just don't get it.

47:51.953 --> 47:53.662
Do you enjoy being that rude?

47:53.746 --> 47:56.248
Because when you do that,

47:56.332 --> 47:58.291
it just gets
underneath my skin,

47:58.376 --> 48:00.460
and it makes me

48:00.545 --> 48:02.921
completely insane!

48:08.427 --> 48:10.387
Thank you, madame, for
the fascinating lesson

48:10.471 --> 48:11.972
in our cultural differences.

48:12.056 --> 48:14.641
I'm sure it would not
betray my duty now

48:14.725 --> 48:17.394
to inform you that your
fiancé and his friend

48:17.478 --> 48:20.105
are no longer our guests.

48:20.982 --> 48:22.816
Well, whose guests
would they be now?

48:26.487 --> 48:28.822
The Carlton Hotel will have
that happy privilege

48:28.906 --> 48:30.490
when they arrive
in Cannes tomorrow.

48:30.575 --> 48:33.785
Perhaps madame wishes to
catch the last train tonight.

48:33.869 --> 48:35.787
I could arrange for
a taxi very quickly.

48:35.871 --> 48:37.205
Yes, thank you.

48:54.724 --> 48:56.308
Bob, I'm losing patience.

49:02.106 --> 49:04.482
A big fish just returned
from the United States.

49:06.652 --> 49:08.820
Luc Teyssier... your friend, right?

49:11.699 --> 49:14.117
Ask him about a stolen necklace.

49:14.410 --> 49:15.702
He won't be hard to find.

49:15.786 --> 49:17.245
Take a look.

49:20.416 --> 49:21.708
You're welcome.

49:27.590 --> 49:28.673
Allons-y!

50:05.127 --> 50:08.088
I come to make peace
with your people.

50:09.965 --> 50:12.509
So you're still after Charlie?

50:12.593 --> 50:13.593
It is incredible.

50:13.678 --> 50:16.513
I admire your persistence.
It's so American.

50:16.597 --> 50:18.264
I am not an American.

50:18.349 --> 50:21.267
I'm a soon-to-be
ex-American Canadian.

50:21.352 --> 50:23.436
May I help you with your bag?

50:23.521 --> 50:24.938
No, maybe not.

50:25.272 --> 50:28.566
I am feeling some very
strange emotions for me.

50:28.651 --> 50:30.276
Guilt. Remorse.

50:30.361 --> 50:32.570
My self-esteem is rock bottom.

50:32.655 --> 50:35.115
What can I do to say I'm sorry?

50:35.199 --> 50:36.408
Shut up!

50:36.492 --> 50:38.410
You haven't spent
60 seconds with me

50:38.494 --> 50:39.774
when you weren't
after something.

50:39.787 --> 50:41.871
What's it this time,
buy, sell, or trade?

50:41.956 --> 50:44.541
True, I used you a lot.

50:44.625 --> 50:46.042
You helped me to get my vine,

50:46.127 --> 50:48.378
and I left you with nothing.

50:48.462 --> 50:51.339
What can I do to
make it up to you?

50:51.424 --> 50:53.425
Now I'm here for you.

50:57.304 --> 50:58.972
Typical.

51:05.896 --> 51:07.188
Who put this here?

52:47.790 --> 52:49.916
So I asked myself
what I can possibly do

52:50.000 --> 52:51.167
to make it up to you,

52:51.252 --> 52:52.669
so I buy this ticket,

52:52.753 --> 52:53.837
and voila, here I am...

52:53.921 --> 52:56.756
Quiet.

53:13.774 --> 53:16.317
You come, you go,

53:16.402 --> 53:18.319
you promise one thing,
you do something else.

53:18.404 --> 53:20.363
Why should I believe you?

53:20.447 --> 53:22.532
Because I have
no reason to lie now.

53:22.616 --> 53:24.033
Do I look like the kind...

53:24.118 --> 53:25.451
You look like the kind

53:25.536 --> 53:28.371
who steals airplane
liquor bottles,

53:28.455 --> 53:30.790
who offers a girl a ride,
then has to steal a car

53:30.875 --> 53:32.125
in order to give it to her,

53:32.209 --> 53:36.379
the kind who puts a plant
in a person's bag.

53:36.463 --> 53:38.423
This is a no-smoking
compartment.

53:39.341 --> 53:41.718
OK, I stop. Voila. For you.

53:41.802 --> 53:43.303
See, I'm changing, I'm growing.

53:43.387 --> 53:44.554
We help each other.

53:44.638 --> 53:46.472
I don't need your help.

53:46.557 --> 53:50.101
Do you have a plan for
when you see Charlie?

53:50.185 --> 53:51.269
Still no?

53:51.353 --> 53:52.520
You're going into a battle,

53:52.605 --> 53:55.106
you have no strategy,
no armor, no bullshit?

53:55.232 --> 53:57.650
I don't need bullshit
to get Charlie back.

53:57.735 --> 54:00.153
Just a little.
It might be handy.

54:00.237 --> 54:02.155
For me, bullshit
is like breathing.

54:02.239 --> 54:05.450
I stay. I help you.
I promise, OK.?

54:05.534 --> 54:07.368
Do what you want.
It's a free country.

54:07.453 --> 54:08.536
Isn't it?

54:08.621 --> 54:10.747
Well, oui.

54:18.464 --> 54:19.464
Is... is that Charlie?

54:20.633 --> 54:22.133
Can I...

54:27.848 --> 54:29.641
How did you meet?

54:29.725 --> 54:31.059
At a party.

54:31.143 --> 54:33.186
I'd just come to Toronto
on a teaching exchange.

54:33.270 --> 54:34.646
We started talking,

54:34.730 --> 54:37.148
and I had this
feeling about him.

54:37.232 --> 54:39.150
It wasn't exactly a thunderclap

54:39.234 --> 54:41.736
or a lightning bolt.
It was more like a...

54:41.820 --> 54:43.237
Light drizzle?

54:44.198 --> 54:45.448
You really, honestly,

54:45.532 --> 54:46.783
never had that feeling
about anybody

54:46.867 --> 54:48.201
in your whole entire life?

54:48.285 --> 54:50.703
If I did, I would not admit it.

54:50.788 --> 54:53.706
His chin looks a little
weak, if you ask me.

54:53.791 --> 54:54.916
It doesn't, and I didn't.

54:55.000 --> 54:56.584
Why wouldn't you
admit that feeling?

54:56.669 --> 54:58.628
Why? Look where it's got you.

54:58.712 --> 54:59.837
Maybe if you did,

54:59.922 --> 55:02.966
you wouldn't have
that little problem.

55:03.050 --> 55:05.927
It's not a problem.
It's just a temporary...

55:06.887 --> 55:08.721
There's something in his eyes.

55:08.806 --> 55:10.431
Vain, it is a word, no?

55:10.516 --> 55:12.475
It is a word.
He has beautiful eyes.

55:12.559 --> 55:13.935
And he knows it.

55:14.019 --> 55:15.395
You can see it in his smile.

55:15.479 --> 55:18.690
Not even a smile.
A smirk. Is a word?

55:18.774 --> 55:21.484
Shut up. Is it a word?

55:21.568 --> 55:23.319
Two words, no?

55:23.404 --> 55:24.737
Why are you chasing after him

55:24.822 --> 55:25.947
after what he's done?

55:26.031 --> 55:27.198
Because I love him,

55:27.282 --> 55:29.742
and I'm afraid if he
doesn't come back

55:29.827 --> 55:32.662
that I'll... It'll hurt so much

55:32.746 --> 55:33.955
that I'll shrivel up

55:34.039 --> 55:36.499
and never be able
to love ever again.

55:36.583 --> 55:37.959
You say that now,

55:38.043 --> 55:42.005
but after a time,
you would forget.

55:42.089 --> 55:44.215
First, you would
forget his chin,

55:44.299 --> 55:46.175
and then his nose,

55:46.260 --> 55:48.344
and after a while,
you would struggle

55:48.429 --> 55:50.888
to remember the exact
color of his eyes.

55:50.973 --> 55:53.850
One day you wake up,
and... he's gone,

55:53.934 --> 55:57.478
his voice, his smell,
his face...

55:57.563 --> 55:59.272
He will have left you.

55:59.356 --> 56:01.899
And then you can begin again.

57:22.106 --> 57:23.523
Charlie?

58:48.442 --> 58:49.775
Hey!

58:49.860 --> 58:52.361
I can't seem to get
enough of this cheese,

58:52.446 --> 58:55.239
and I haven't eaten
this stuff in years.

58:55.324 --> 58:57.450
You don't look like
you got much sleep.

58:57.534 --> 58:58.618
Un café.

58:59.912 --> 59:00.995
For some reason,

59:01.079 --> 59:02.830
I just feel
incredibly refreshed.

59:02.915 --> 59:05.541
I had this dream, which
I can't remember really.

59:05.626 --> 59:07.710
You know when you have a dream

59:07.794 --> 59:09.212
that is just delicious

59:09.296 --> 59:10.296
and you wake up

59:10.380 --> 59:13.049
and you feel all transformed?

59:14.259 --> 59:16.510
God, it's beautiful here.

59:17.596 --> 59:19.180
Merci.

59:20.933 --> 59:22.141
Did you know

59:22.226 --> 59:24.101
that there are 452
official government cheeses

59:24.186 --> 59:25.228
in this country?

59:25.312 --> 59:26.979
Don't you think
that's incredible,

59:27.064 --> 59:29.523
to come up with 452 ways
of classifying

59:29.608 --> 59:32.443
what is basically
a bacterial process?

59:32.527 --> 59:33.861
You would prefer one cheese,

59:33.946 --> 59:35.404
one cheeseburger to put it on,

59:35.489 --> 59:37.073
and one restaurant
to eat it in?

59:37.157 --> 59:39.617
I'm saying I like the cheese.

59:41.036 --> 59:42.411
God!

59:42.496 --> 59:45.164
What side of the train
did you wake up on?

59:46.083 --> 59:48.584
God, it's beautiful here!

59:51.630 --> 59:53.047
What? What's that face?

59:53.131 --> 59:54.882
You don't think it's beautiful?

59:54.967 --> 59:57.426
You don't think
this is beautiful?

59:59.846 --> 01:00:00.888
What?

01:00:01.765 --> 01:00:03.683
I was born here.

01:00:05.560 --> 01:00:06.686
Really?

01:00:08.355 --> 01:00:10.439
But this is so beautiful
and so charming.

01:00:11.316 --> 01:00:13.609
It was too beautiful for me,

01:00:13.694 --> 01:00:15.111
I had to leave.

01:00:24.454 --> 01:00:26.122
Oh, god.

01:00:26.206 --> 01:00:27.707
Oh, god!

01:00:28.041 --> 01:00:29.959
What?

01:00:30.043 --> 01:00:31.460
I'm going to die.

01:00:31.545 --> 01:00:32.962
What, what, the cheese?

01:00:33.046 --> 01:00:36.799
Don't say it.
Stop that rocking.

01:00:36.883 --> 01:00:38.092
Stop the rocking.

01:00:38.176 --> 01:00:40.094
